# Component Page Structure

All component documentation pages must follow this layout (see Accordion page as reference):

## Main Layout

- **Two-column grid**: `grid grid-cols-2 gap-x-10 gap-y-10`
- **Row 1 left column**: DocHeader (title, description) + TabBar
- **Row 1 right column**: Empty (content starts in row 2)
- **Content**: Starts in row 2, below the tab group

## Section Structure

### Overview / heading sections
- Place in left column: `col-start-1`
- Used for Overview text, Accessibility, Behavior, etc.

### Tables
- Always span full width: `col-span-2`
- Use `variant="surface"` and `hideTitle` on DocTable (no table headings)

### Examples
- **Layout**: `grid grid-cols-2 gap-10 items-stretch`
- **One example left, one right** (paired comparisons)
- **DocPreview props**: `rounded={false}` `border={false}` `verticalPaddingOnly` `aspectSquare`
- **No heading** on DocPreview (no title prop)
- **Width/height**: Add `className="h-full min-h-0"` to DocPreview so examples are square and fill column
- Inner content: `w-full max-w-*` so example spans column width

### Gap
- Use `gap-10` between columns in example grids

## Tab Content

- Overview, Design Tokens, Styles, Properties each render as direct children of the main grid
- Wrap each section in `col-span-2` when it should span full width
- Design Tokens: Color Tokens in first row below tabs; all tables span horizontally
- Properties: Wrap entire tab content in `col-span-2`; content starts below tabs
